    "created_at": "2016-09-08T16:20:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-08T16:20:46Z",
    "body": "Closing this out for now, this doesn't seem possible without breaking existing apps.\n\nIf we inject a `Buffer` argument to the `require` function wrapper than any preload scripts or internal/downstream modules doing `const {Buffer} = require('buffer')` will break, [example](https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/a634554fca562e82d326967b809325f8ee5d3acd/lib/util.js#L4).\n\nIf we remove it completely as a global when `nodeIntegration` is `false` then preload scripts and downstream modules used by preload scripts assuming it is globally available will break.\n\nThe best workaround for now is for apps to delete it themselves in their own preload scripts when it is unneeded or breaking existing site functionality. \n"
  },
