    "created_at": "2016-09-08T17:11:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-08T17:11:01Z",
    "body": "> The best workaround for now is for apps to delete it themselves in their own preload scripts when it is unneeded or breaking existing site functionality.\n\n@kevinsawicki Without the changes in this PR however users won't be able to delete it without Electron internally throwing errors as Electron itself is one of those things that assumes it is global.  Can we resurrect this PR and\n- Replace all instances of global assumption of `Buffer` inside Electron with `require('buffer')`\n- Not delete `Buffer` from the global scope but add docs somewhere that indicate this is recommended, possibly even add a `console.warn` somewhere to inform people of this newly discovered issue.\n"
  },
